			Logger message object contains complete message details including time stamp, message text, message category, identity of the message provider, context cycle in which the message was posted.			
		</summary>				
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><BitSize>1600</BitSize><SubItem><Name>TimeStamp</Name><Type>DATE_AND_TIME</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>0</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Text</Name><Type>STRING(160)</Type><BitSize>1288</BitSize><BitOffs>32</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Identity</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><BitOffs>1344</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Category</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">eMessageCategory</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>1408</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Cycle</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><BitOffs>1472</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>PerCycleCount</Name><Type>BYTE</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>1536</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>ExpectDequeing</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>1544</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>MessageDigest</Name><Type>DWORD</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>1568</BitOffs></SubItem></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="TcoCore">TcoLogger</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
		<docu>
			<summary>
				Default implementation of Logger.	
				<note type="tip">
					 This type is partially extended by IVF to retrieve messages from the logger in IVF application.			
				</note>												 
			</summary>		
			<code>
			   // Intializes message retrieval into applications logger
				..._logger.StartLoggingMessages(eMessageCategory.All);
			</code>
			<code>
				FUNCTION_BLOCK LoggerUsage EXTENDS TcoCore.TcoObject
				VAR
					_logger : TcoCore.TcoLogger(THIS^);
					_counter : INT;
				END_VAR
				//---------------------------------------------
				_counter := _counter + 1;
				IF((_counter MOD 100) = 0) THEN
					_logger.Push('hey friend! we got a problem', eMessageCategory.Critical);
				END_IF;	
			</code>		
		</docu>
~]]></Comment><BitSize>1608448</BitSize><ExtendsType Namespace="TcoCore">TcoObject</ExtendsType><Implements Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoLogger</Implements><SubItem><Name>_buffer</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">TcoLogItem</Type><ArrayInfo><LBound>0</LBound><Elements>1001</Elements></ArrayInfo><BitSize>1601600</BitSize><BitOffs>6784</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_plcCarret</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>1608384</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_minLoggingLevel</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">eMessageCategory</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>1608400</BitOffs><Default><EnumText>eMessageCategory.Notification</EnumText></Default></SubItem><SubItem><Name>MAX_MESSAGE_BUFFER_INDEX</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>1608416</BitOffs><Default><Value>1000</Value></Default></SubItem><Method><Name>PushMessage</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
		<docu>
			<summary>
				Pushes the message to logging buffer.
				See also `Push`
				<note type="important">
						This method is typically invoked from a `TcoMessenger`. 
						Depending on settings of the messenger the messages can be logged on rising edge of the message, to prevent buffer overrun.
						For details see `TcoMessengerSettings`.
				</note>				 
			</summary>				
		</docu>
~]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>inMessage</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">TcoMessage</Type><BitSize>1600</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Method><Name>Push</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
		<docu>
			<summary>
				Pushes the message to logging buffer.
				See also `PushMessage`
				<note:important>When using this method in a cyclical environment the message will be push each time it is called. You may easily overrun the logging buffer.</note>				 
			</summary>				
		</docu>
~]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>Text</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
